headlines.description: — Seth Curry scored 23 points, Tyrese Maxey added 20 and the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers beat the Detroit Pistons 109-98 on Thursday night for their fifth straight win.
— Jordan Clarkson was coming off one of his worst games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson scores 30, Mitchell-less Jazz rout Hawks 116-98

headlines.description: — Whatever the Boston Celtics said at that team dinner a few days ago clearly worked.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics crank up defense again, roll past Heat 95-78

headlines.description: — JaVale McGee has played just seven games for the Phoenix Suns and has already become a fan favorite in the desert. At 7-feet tall with long arms, long legs and a tendency to throw his body all over the court, the veteran's stints in the game are...
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 27, Suns pull away to beat Rockets 123-111

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 11 of his 28 points in the fourth quarter, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rallied from a 19-point deficit to beat the Los Angeles Lakers for the second time this season, 107-104 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder roar back to beat Lakers again, 107-104
